    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen using block selection to delete characters, such that some lines are unaffected, on_lines receives the byte count of the affected lines only, and not the whole range.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- Have a buffer with\r\n  ```\r\n  ab\r\n  c\r\n  de\r\n  ```\r\n- Attach on_lines listener, `vim.api.nvim_buf_attach(0, false, { on_lines = print })`.\r\n- Use visual-block mode to delete a column from `b` to `e` (for ex. `ggg_<C-v>2jx`).\r\n- Listener reports `lines <buf> <tick> 0 3 3 6`.\r\n\r\nThe \"byte count of previous contents\", reported as 6, is incorrect. It counts only lines 0 and 2. Moreover, if the change is undone and redone, the listener correctly reports 8 bytes.\r\n\r\nThis is problematic as it makes it impossible to correctly track incremental changes without keeping a copy of the buffer.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nByte count of changed contents should include all lines in range.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nofficial Arch extra repository",
